==================================================
PILLAR #3: STORY-BASED LEARNING
==================================================

Sentences should lead to stories.

The platform should not feel like endless sentence drilling.

Stories provide context and make language memorable.

The learning flow should be:

Learn Sentences
→ Unlock Story
→ Read Story
→ Save Story Sentences
→ Review Sentences

Stories should intentionally reuse previously learned sentence patterns.

The learner should feel:

"I already understand many of these sentences."

instead of:

"I have no idea what I'm reading."

==================================================
STORY FEATURES
==================================================

Each story contains:

- Title
- Topic
- Difficulty
- Estimated reading time
- Story text
- Translation
- Audio
- Vocabulary highlights
- Key sentences
- Save sentence button
- Comprehension quiz
- Coin rewards

Story categories:

- Travel
- Daily Life
- Family
- Friendship
- Workplace
- School
- Adventure
- Mystery
- Romance
- Humor
- Culture

Story lengths:

A1: 100-150 words

A2: 150-250 words

B1: 250-400 words

B2+: 400-700 words

==================================================
SPACED REPETITION SYSTEM
==================================================

Every sentence has a review state:

- New
- Learning
- Review
- Mastered

User ratings:

- Again
- Hard
- Good
- Easy

Review scheduling:

Again:
Review today

Hard:
Review tomorrow

Good:
Review in 3 days

Easy:
Review in 7 days

Dashboard should always show:

- Reviews due
- New sentences available
- Stories available
- Coins available to earn

==================================================
SHADOWING SYSTEM
==================================================

Users can practice shadowing.

Flow:

1. Listen
2. Repeat
3. Listen Again
4. Repeat Again
5. Self Rate

Options:

- Normal Speed
- Slow Speed
- Auto Replay
- Loop Sentence

